Per the instructions provided in the Take-Home Project

Approach: Originally tried building a web-based OCR utilizing JavaScript and programming assistance from Gemini AI.  But troubleshooting issues that came up proved time consuming and problematic due to my lack of knowledge with JavaScript.  So I turned to a language I am more familiar with; AutoIt.  With assistance once again from Gemini AI a new prototype was created, but it is currently incomplete.  I built the current code into separate modules for readability and easy modification so future updates and changes can be readily added.  Currently, it can process image labels stored in a directory and output the text it finds into another.  Due to time restrictions and severely limited budget I was unable to refine the OCR processing to an acceptable enough level to implement TTB checking.

Tools Used: AutoIt and Gemini AI for quicker code building

Assumptions: 

1. The utility intended for the tool is supposed to help reduce the amount of human oversight needed, not to eliminate it.  For this I would want to see how TTB agents currently check labels and get their input on the "good and the bad" about the process.

2. The tool should be able to run on any OS.  This was why I tried for a web based version originally.

3. A straightforward UI.  The interface should make it obvious how the tool should be used.

4. The tool should be able to offload as much of the reduntant steps from the user.  And if possible, implement a form of AI to help with it.  This step would require much more time and a budget, among other things.
